<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN TELLS OF RAPE, SLAYING BY 2 GUNMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two gunmen approached a couple in a car parked in Mission Hills early Christmas 
Day, shot the man to death and raped his woman companion, the woman told Los 
Angeles police. 
</P>
<P>
A passerby noticed the body of Elmer Rudy Alvarado, 26, of Highland Park 
slumped in the front seat of a car on Tupper Street near Lemona Avenue on 
Tuesday morning, police said. 
</P>
<P>
"He had been shot at least once in the upper portion of his body," Officer 
Marlene Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
A woman contacted police shortly after the body was found and said she had been 
sitting in the car with Alvarado when two men approached and shot him. She said 
the gunmen then forced her to go to a vacant lot in Mission Hills and raped 
her, Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was hospitalized in good condition, police said. 
</P>
<P>
No other details of the incident were available, Johnson said. 
</P>
