<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: N. HOLLYWOOD WOMAN IDENTIFIED IN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman killed when her car struck a utility pole in Van Nuys has been 
identified as Martha Nunez, 53, of North Hollywood, Los Angeles police reported 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Nunez may have been having car problems when her auto ran a red light Monday on 
Sepulveda Boulevard at Victory Boulevard and sideswiped another car before 
crashing, Officer Leona Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
"Witnesses said she was going about 55 or 60 miles per hour through the 
intersection . . . waving her hands and honking her horn like she was trying to 
warn people," Thomas said. "We don't know for sure what happened, yet, but it's 
possible that her accelerator was stuck." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122690-0018 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 327224 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 26, 1990, Wednesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 8; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Tree Lights Blamed in Fire: Marisa Ramos wipes away tears Tuesday as 
firefighters inspect damage at her rented house in the 7800 block of Cantaloupe 
Avenue in Van Nuys. L.A. City Fire Department spokesman Jim Wells said a 
short-circuit in Christmas tree lights set off the fire that left the residence 
uninhabitable. Ramos was awakened about 8 a.m. by a window breaking from the 
heat, and she and visitor Angela Garzon of Venezuela fled. "We lost 
everything," said Ramos, who shared the house with a brother who was away. KEN 
LUBAS / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
