<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: PEOPLEWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and international 
news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Clay's Base Humor: A spokesman for Andrew Dice Clay said the comedian has been 
banned by military officials from visiting two Air Force bases in Texas and 
Louisiana. 
</P>
<P>
According to press agent Michael Levine -- who claims an informal poll revealed 
Clay to be the most requested entertainer by American troops in Saudi Arabia -- 
Clay was upset by the military snub. Said Clay: "I'm really disappointed. 
There's nobody more patriotic than me, and when I heard the troops wanted me, I 
very much wanted to go. I hope there's some base out there that will let me 
visit." 
</P>
