<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCENE ON THE STREET EAR THEY GO AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SYBIL BAKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some earrings make a whisper of a fashion statement. Single pearls. Teensy gold 
hearts. Discreet silver circles. Heck, you pull off your sweater and you don't 
even know if they're still in your ears or have burrowed into the cable stitch. 
</P>
<P>
And then there are EARRINGS. These are fashion statements that carry across the 
room -- some of them in a shout that's, well, almost earsplitting. 
</P>
<P>
If you want to see EARRINGS, try the streets and malls of Pasadena and West 
Covina, where they are much in evidence. And among the young, the dramatic 
effect of one earring is duplicated, or in some cases enhanced, with one or 
more earrings. 
</P>
<P>
Women who believe that lobe makes the world go round put all the focus just on 
one ear. And women who refuse to let fashion lead them by the nose can also 
prove it. SYBIL BAKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, earrings ; Photo, earrings ; Photo, earrings ; Photo, nose rings ALEX 
KOESTER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
