<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL; 
</P>
<P>
CAMPBELL, WALSH BEST OF ALL-CITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carson High quarterback John Walsh and Poly running back Jonathan Campbell were 
selected City players of the year in the 4-A and 3-A Divisions, respectively, 
to highlight the 54th annual All-City football teams selected by Los Angeles 
area sportswriters. 
</P>
<P>
Walsh, who led the Colts to the 4-A Division title with a 12-1 record, set 
state single-season records with 4,206 passing yards and 48 touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
He completed 229 of 388 passes and threw for more than 300 yards in eight 
games. 
</P>
<P>
Carson had the most players on the 4-A Division team with nine, followed by 
Dorsey and Banning with four apiece. Tailback/quarterback Lamont Warren of 
Dorsey, last season's player of the year, heads a list of five returning 
All-City selections in the 4-A Division. He is joined by defensive back Derrick 
Stewart of Granada Hills, running back Ontiwaun Carter of Kennedy and defensive 
linemen Marcus Long and Bob Tuitau of Carson. 
</P>
<P>
Campbell, who led the Parrots' to the 3-A Division title with an 11-3 record, 
gained a school-record 2,091 yards, an average of 149.4 a game, with 31 
touchdowns. In Poly's last five games of the season, Campbell rushed for 865 
yards in 139 carries and scored eight touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
He rushed for 200 yards and scored two touchdowns in the Parrots' 28-8 victory 
over Lincoln in the 3-A Division title game. 
</P>
<P>
Poly, which had never won a City football title before, had two other players, 
offensive lineman Edward Moraino and defensive back Raul Torres, on the 3-A 
Division team. 
</P>
<P>
* ALL-CITY SELECTIONS: C12 
</P>
</TEXT>
