<TEXT>
<P>
Dollar Climbs in Tokyo: The dollar rose against the yen as stock prices fell in 
sluggish trading in Tokyo amid concerns about the Middle East and political 
problems in the Soviet Union. The dollar closed at 135.95 yen, up 0.25 yen from 
Friday's close of 135.70 yen. 
</P>
<P>
Financial markets were closed on Monday for a national holiday. Dealers said 
most investors are waiting until next year to make any new moves. "If there 
should be any move, the only possibility is upward for the dollar," said 
Chizuko Satsukawa, a dealer at Chemical Bank. On the Tokyo stock exchange, the 
stronger dollar, lower bond prices and worries about the Persian Gulf and the 
Soviet Union helped push the Nikkei average down 351.72 to 23,767.88 points. 
Investors tend to buy the dollar as a safe haven in times of international 
turmoil. European markets were closed. 
