<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ROMANIA; 
</P>
<P>
COUNTRY'S FORMER KING IS DEPORTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Romania's former King Michael was deported less than 12 hours after arriving in 
Bucharest on his first visit since Communist rulers forced him to abdicate 43 
years ago. Michael, 69, had returned a year after the revolution that saw the 
ouster and execution of dictator Nicolae Ceausescu. Michael was forced to 
return to Switzerland, where he lives in exile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122690-0077 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 327431 </DOCID>
