ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
CITY OKS PROPOSAL TO IMPROVE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY PAULSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City planners recently approved a $2-million proposal for improving the 
Interstate 5 interchange at Camino de Estrella. 
</P>
<P>
Heavy traffic congestion along San Clemente's northernmost thoroughfare, which 
is known as Camino de los Mares east of the freeway, has forced traffic 
engineers to propose widening the road by 100 feet and installing eight new, 
synchronized traffic signals. 
</P>
<P>
Also being proposed is the widening of the southbound freeway off-ramp to 
Camino de Estrella in order to provide a left-turn lane. 
</P>
<P>
If the project is approved by the City Council, the changes are expected to be 
under way by spring 1991, according to traffic engineer Akram Hindeyeh. WENDY 
PAULSON 
