<P>
DRIVE-BY SHOOTING KILLS SANTA ANA MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man was fatally shot on a street corner Tuesday in what police said was a 
drive-by shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Jorge Espinoza, 26, of Santa Ana was shot once in the chest about 10:40 a.m. 
near an apartment complex at Bristol and Walnut streets. He staggered around 
the corner before collapsing behind a bus-stop bench outside 124 S. Bristol 
St., Police Sgt. Dan Beaumarchais said. 
</P>
