INSTEAD: County firefighters will help in the effort to "recycle" trees. 
</P>
<P>
Following the lead of Irvine and Orange last year, six other cities will pick 
up discarded Christmas trees and grind each one into about a bucketful of 
garden mulch. . . . The process saves dwindling landfill space. "The flocked 
trees we do not need; they gum up the machinery," a spokeswoman said. . . . New 
to the effort his year: Costa Mesa, Fountain Valley, Laguna Niguel, Los 
Alamitos, Mission Viejo, Seal Beach. Call your city hall for information. Tom 
Hamilton and Mark Landsbaum 
