<P>
EMERGENCY TEAM SAVES PANDAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Emergency medical care at a Chinese zoo saved two star performing pandas that 
had become critically ill because of intestinal problems, an official newspaper 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The Liberation Daily said today that the pandas at the Fuzhou Zoo in 
southeastern Fujian province were near death when their condition was diagnosed 
as acute intestinal inflammation and intestinal blockage. 
</P>
<P>
The diagnosis was made early this month after zoo officials held urgent 
consultations with medical and animal experts, the newspaper said. After nine 
days of special treatment, Qingqing and Yuanyuan recovered, it said. 
</P>
<P>
Qingqing, 15, and Yuanyuan, 9, have performed for audiences around the world, 
including stops in the United States, Australia and Hong Kong. Their popular 
stunts include riding bicycles, doing somersaults and dunking a basketball. 
</P>
</TEXT>
