<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIZ SMITH: THREATS PROVIDE BELATED ENDING TO EXPOSE ON TRUMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LIZ SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AFTER THIS column broke the scoop last week that former Trump executive Jack 
O'Donnell will bring out a hot and sizzling expose sometime next spring -- a 
book to be titled "Trumped! The Decline &amp; Fall of Donald Trump" -- I 
received a call from Jack. 
</P>
<P>
He said: "You know, Liz, I had no ending for my book, no denouement. But after 
your story appeared in print, Donald sent lawyers here to my office to threaten 
me. They said he would accuse me of being a morally lax person and all kinds of 
other stuff. They made intimidating threats that weren't even thinly veiled. 
</P>
<P>
"You know, I had not used the book to include all the things I knew about 
Donald's use of pressure to get whatever he wants. I had left most of that out 
and did not bear down on it. But this was just the last straw. Thank you for 
giving me the press that provided an ending to my book." 
</P>
<P>
YOU CAN see Ivana Trump and Marla Maples in People magazine's "Most Intriguing 
of 1990" year-end issue, under an amusing headline, "Marla vs. Ivana: How to 
Tell Them Apart." Sample "Marla looks 35, is 27. . . . Ivana looks 35, is 41." 
</P>
<P>
Ivana did not hold her annual all-girl Christmas lunch this year. Instead, her 
pal Kathy Keaton gave a small private celebration for Ivana and her mother, 
Maria, in the marble palace Kathy occupies with hubby Bob Guccione on 
Manhattan's East Side. (Kathy is the tycoon publisher-editor of Omni and 
Longevity magazines.) 
</P>
<P>
Lunch began with heaps of caviar and went on to bigger and better things. Each 
of the privileged few received a terrific flagon of designer Pauline Trigere's 
hard-to-get perfume "Liquid Chic." (You have to buy this from Pauline direct.) 
</P>
<P>
Ivana says she was going to Aspen with the children after Christmas because she 
made reservations there months ago. At the time, she had no idea Marla also 
planned to return. Ivana is not, as reported elsewhere, going to Palm Beach. 
</P>
</TEXT>
