<P>
MASUR RECEIVES EUROPEAN AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FRANKFURT, Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kurt Masur, who will become director of the New York Philharmonic next fall, 
has been named European of the Year by an international jury in Paris, the 
French weekly La Vie announced Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Masur, 63, who is at present director of the Gewandhaus Orchestra in Leipzig, 
was cited for his influence on the development of a peaceful revolution in East 
Germany. 
</P>
<P>
He was selected in April to succeed the late Leonard Bernstein at the New York 
Philharmonic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
